                    <h4>Response</h4>
                    <p>A comprehensive recovery program includes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Captive breeding and release programs</li>
                        <li>Habitat protection and management at breeding and migration sites</li>
                        <li>Predator control programs</li>
                        <li>Supplemental feeding at key sites</li>
                        <li>Cross-fostering experiments with related species</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>Outcomes</h4>
                    <p>While the species remains critically endangered, intensive management has prevented immediate extinction. The 2021-2022 breeding season saw the highest number of wild-born chicks in over a decade.</p>
